<subSubSection id="C3474F9DFFFA3E58428FE81D28BAFEC7" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="63" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BE21C16FFFA3E59428FE81D2E24F8B1" blockId="0.[146,1431,1807,2027]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis id="B929C004FFFA3E59428FE81D2D17F8C8" bold="true" box="[146,301,1807,1833]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Distribution</emphasis>
:—The species was introduced to Xiamen Botanical Garden from 
<collectingRegion id="4999D2F4FFFA3E594655E81D291AF8C8" box="[1096,1312,1807,1833]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Guizhou Province</collectingRegion>
in 1970s, but the exact locality is unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE21C16FFFA3E5942DCE84E2D2AF80A" blockId="0.[146,1431,1807,2027]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis id="B929C004FFFA3E5942DCE84E2D87F897" bold="true" box="[193,445,1884,1910]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Conservation status</emphasis>
:—This species is so far only known from cultivated plants in Xiamen Botanical Garden. Because no data are available on its distribution in the wild, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D6795FFFA3E59461EE8962942F87F" authorityName="C. H. Zheng, N. H. Xia &amp; Y. F. Deng" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="C. H. Zheng, N. H. Xia &amp; Y. F. Deng" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[1027,1400,1924,1950]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ampelocalamus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stoloniformis">
<emphasis id="B929C004FFFA3E59461EE8962942F87F" box="[1027,1400,1924,1950]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="62">Ampelocalamus stoloniformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is provisionally considered to be Data Deficient (DD) according to the 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCC61E7FFFA3E5941F7E8B828B4F825" author="IUCN" box="[1002,1166,1962,1988]" pageId="0" pageNumber="62" refId="ref1274" refString="IUCN (2001) IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria, Version 3.1. Prepared by the IUCN Species Survival Commission. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland, and Cambridge, United Kingdom. 30 pp." type="book" year="2001">IUCN (2001)</bibRefCitation>
Red List criteria and categories.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE21C16FFFB3E5842DBEF8528BAFEC7" blockId="1.[151,1436,151,294]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis id="B929C004FFFB3E5842DBEF852D36FF50" bold="true" box="[198,268,151,177]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Notes</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D6795FFFB3E58432FEF8A2EB5FF53" authorityName="C. H. Zheng, N. H. Xia &amp; Y. F. Deng" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="C. H. Zheng, N. H. Xia &amp; Y. F. Deng" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[306,655,152,178]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ampelocalamus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stoloniformis">
<emphasis id="B929C004FFFB3E58432FEF8A2EB5FF53" box="[306,655,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Ampelocalamus stoloniformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D6795FFFB3E584137EF8A2FDEFF53" box="[810,996,152,178]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ampelocalamus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microphyllus">
<emphasis id="B929C004FFFB3E584137EF8A2FDEFF53" box="[810,996,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">A. microphyllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in its culms 
<quantity id="4CA5B1F3FFFB3E584719EF8A295EFF53" box="[1284,1380,152,178]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3–6 mm</quantity>
(not 
<quantity id="4CA5B1F3FFFB3E58428AEFAC2D30FF39" box="[151,266,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="10.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="5.0">5–15 mm</quantity>
) in diameter, internodes (5–) 
<quantity id="4CA5B1F3FFFB3E584079EFAC2EE0FF39" box="[612,730,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.55" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" unit="cm" value="15.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="13.0">13–18 cm</quantity>
(not 
<quantity id="4CA5B1F3FFFB3E584107EFAC2FA8FF39" box="[794,914,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" unit="cm" value="25.0" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="15.0">15–35 cm</quantity>
) long, ligule of the culm sheath ca. 
<quantity id="4CA5B1F3FFFB3E58475CEFAC29A6FF39" box="[1345,1436,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
(not ca. 
<quantity id="4CA5B1F3FFFB3E5842EBEFF72D01FF1E" box="[246,315,229,255]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
) long, ligule of the leaf ca. 
<quantity id="4CA5B1F3FFFB3E584061EFF72EFAFF1E" box="[636,704,229,255]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
(not ca. 
<quantity id="4CA5B1F3FFFB3E58413BEFF72F51FF1E" box="[806,875,229,255]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
) long, and leaf blades 2–6 × 
<quantity id="4CA5B1F3FFFB3E5846A3EFF7297BFF1E" box="[1214,1345,229,255]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" unit="cm" value="0.44999999999999996" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.6 cm</quantity>
(not 3– 9 × 0.4–1.0 cm) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCC61E7FFFB3E58437DEE1E2E09FEC7" author="Hsueh, C. R. &amp; Yi, T. P." box="[352,563,268,294]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" pagination="68 - 73" refId="ref1235" refString="Hsueh, C. R. &amp; Yi, T. P. (1982) New plants of the genus Sinocalamus from Sichuan. Journal of Yunnan Forestry College 1982 (1): 68 - 73." type="journal article" year="1982">Hsueh &amp; Yi 1982</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCC61E7FFFB3E584022EE1E2F10FEC7" author="Chen, S. H. &amp; Wang, Z. Z." box="[575,810,268,294]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" pagination="10 - 11" refId="ref1086" refString="Chen, S. H. &amp; Wang, Z. Z. (2004) A description of the reproductive organs of Drepanostachyum microphyllum (Hsueh et Yi) Keng f. ex Yi. Journal of Bamboo Research 23 (4): 10 - 11." type="journal article" year="2004">Chen &amp; Wang 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCC61E7FFFB3E58412BEE1E2F49FEC7" author="Chen, S. H. &amp; Wang, Z. Z." box="[822,883,268,294]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" pagination="307 - 310" refId="ref1135" refString="Chen, S. H. &amp; Wang, Z. Z. (2007) Drepanostachyum stoloniforme S. H. Chen &amp; Z. Z. Wang, a new species of Bambusoideae from China. Acta Phytotaxonomica Sinica 45: 307 - 310. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1360 / aps 06073" type="journal article" year="2007">2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCC61E7FFFB3E584162EE1E2849FEC7" author="Li, D. Z. &amp; Stapleton, C. M. A." box="[895,1139,268,294]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" pagination="97 - 102" refId="ref1482" refString="Li, D. Z. &amp; Stapleton, C. M. A. (2006) Ampelocalamus, Drepanostachyum. In: Wu, Z. Y., Raven, P. &amp; Hong, D. Y. (eds), Flora of China 22. Science Press, Beijing &amp; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis, pp. 97 - 102." type="book chapter" year="2006">Li &amp; Stapleton 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
